rComments: Prof Donovan is knowledgeable...I can safely say that he is the most knowledgeable prof I've had at UofT. I have to agree with the previous reviewer's post that when he asks questions, he is looking for a precise answer. I think this is the result of his 'classical' education and training. He is also very kind, genuine and encouraging.

Fr. Donovan is the best lecturer I've come across.  He is a predictable evaluator.  He comes off as overbearing to a lot of people, and he tends to gravitate towards the more shy, quiet kids in the class.  He certainly knows his stuff, but doesn't allow for creative thinking as a student. Repeat what he says and get an "A".
He played favourites hardcore.  And if you weren't on that list, your chances of doing well weren't so high. He did talk very eloquently like - like he was telling a story or giving a sermon.

nice enough but has OBVIOUS favorites in class. The material is not difficult, and the tests are simple but it's still impossible to do well because he makes it very unclear what answers he's looking for. Same story with the papers - gives the perception of letting students be creative but wants it his way
wonderful professor. best one at U of T.
